Titolo: Ominous Horizons: A Paladin's Calling

Anno: 2001

Descrizione: Ominous Horizons: A Paladin's Calling is a 3D medieval first-person shooter video game developed by N'Lightning Software Development and released in September 2001. The game is the spiritual successor to Catechumen (2000). Ominous Horizons cost over $1.6 million over the course of the game's development cycle, being the highest budgeted Christian video game. The game's poor sales performance, selling 50,000 copies.

Genere: First-person shooter

Valutazione: N/A
